==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wɪt/}}

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[wit#Old English|wit]], from Germanic ''*witjan'', from Indo-European ''*weid-, *wid-'' ‘see, know’.  Cognate with Dutch [[weet]], German [[Witz]], Swedish [[vett]].  Compare [[wise]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Spoken [[humour]], particularly that thought of quickly.
# A person who tells funny anecdotes or jokes.
# (''in plural'' '''wits''') The ability to think quickly.
#:''Aristotle - Wit is educated insolence.''

